  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As an action, you can leap up to half your movement speed in any direction (this does not consume your movement). <br />If you have at least 15 ft. of head start in a straight line, you can leap up to your full movement speed instead. <br />To use this technique, a creature must be within your pouncing range, as you aim to jump onto them.<br />The target must make a Strength saving throw against your Taijutsu Save DC. <br />On a failure, the target is knocked prone, and you can make a single claw attack against them with advantage (Properties like multiattack or light do not apply to this specific attack).<br />Regardless of success or failure, you leap off the target and land in the nearest free space within 5 ft.<br />If you are hidden from the target they have disadvantage on the saving throw.</p>",
